<subSubSection id="055E459AB29D631A92BB106BCB81D149" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="6924349693A93E5197213425E7D720E3" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="27CEBB9A19945CEED06D6CFF1120D251" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
Chile. Region I 
<normalizedToken id="B32C44138283FFC742C9A6346E332521" originalValue="TarapacÃ¡">Tarapaca</normalizedToken>
and Region II Antofagasta: &quot;Peruvia meridionalis: Cobija, Iquiqui et Arica&quot;, 
<emphasis id="D7A96FD819050C9D58CDC2B08339FA10" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">H.Cuming 953</emphasis>
(lectotype, selected by 
<bibRefCitation id="009F653DBDE1D2716C21BF5B5932A181" DOI="https://doi.org/10.31055/1851.2372.v48.n2.6267" author="Plos, A" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la Sociedad Argentina de Botanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="335 - 340" refId="B13" refString="Plos, A, Sancho, G, 2013. Lectotipificaciones en Ophryosporus (Asteraceae, Eupatorieae, Critoniinae). Boletin de la Sociedad Argentina de Botanica 48 (2): 335 - 340, DOI: https://doi.org/10.31055/1851.2372.v48.n2.6267" title="Lectotipificaciones en Ophryosporus (Asteraceae, Eupatorieae, Critoniinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.31055/1851.2372.v48.n2.6267" volume="48" year="2013">Plos and Sancho (2013</bibRefCitation>
: 338): K [K000486684, photo!]; isolectotypes E [E00322766, photo!], GH [GH00010778!], K [K000486685, photo!], P [P02673192, photo!]); remaining syntypes: 
<emphasis id="602DA8F59EA7ED1C1B355C7DFE173292" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Gaudichaud</emphasis>
s.n. (B [probably destroyed, could not be found], F [F1012247, photo!]).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="45768FFBF595120E3F084B7E8F58DFBC" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicName id="832CBE05E90AF77A8EFBB1D4EFDB7419" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Ophryosporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ophryosporus anomalus" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="anomalus">
<emphasis id="436AA5BADBCB7999973CDC944F390407" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Ophryosporus anomalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been cited for Peru (
<bibRefCitation id="8E48B6BD1818EDEE75FB5A045005DB34" author="King, RM" journalOrPublisher="Phytologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="65 - 67" refId="B7" refString="King, RM, Robinson, H, 1972b. Studies in the Eupatorieae (Asteraceae). CXI. Additions to the genus Ophryosporus. Phytologia 25: 65 - 67" title="Studies in the Eupatorieae (Asteraceae). CXI. Additions to the genus Ophryosporus." volume="25" year="1972 b">King and Robinson 1972b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="FEAA3B174FD53D57D35741D398A18656" author="Brako, L" journalOrPublisher="Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="1 - 1286" refId="B1" refString="Brako, L, Zarucchi, JL, 1993. Catalogue of the flowering plants and gymnosperms of Peru. Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 45: 1 - 1286" title="Catalogue of the flowering plants and gymnosperms of Peru." volume="45" year="1993">Brako and Zarucchi 1993</bibRefCitation>
), likely due to the type collection label (&quot;Peruvia meridionalis...&quot;). However, the localities mentioned there (&quot;...Cobija, Iquiqui et Arica&quot;) are now situated in Chile, and all other reports originate from the coastal zone around Tocopilla (
<bibRefCitation id="C3E8C449509CB6033AADDBBB02E319BB" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Revista Chilena de Historia Natural" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="4 - 8" refId="B5" refString="Johnston, IM, 1932. New records for the flora of the Nitrate Coast. Revista Chilena de Historia Natural 36: 4 - 8" title="New records for the flora of the Nitrate Coast." volume="36" year="1932">Johnston 1932</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E1973F73D4FA05394DD46E7A32F42887" author="Jaffuel, PF" journalOrPublisher="Revista Chilena de Historia Natural" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="265 - 274" refId="B3" refString="Jaffuel, PF, 1936. Excursiones botanicas a los alrededores de Tocopilla. Revista Chilena de Historia Natural 40: 265 - 274" title="Excursiones botanicas a los alrededores de Tocopilla." volume="40" year="1936">Jaffuel 1936</bibRefCitation>
) and therefore 
<bibRefCitation id="0EC0D4B0565F21C4AC8D09B7E9D473C5" author="Luebert, F" journalOrPublisher="Boletin del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="27 - 52" refId="B9" refString="Luebert, F, Garcia, N, Schulz, N, 2007. Observaciones sobre la flora y vegetacion de los alrededores de Tocopilla (22Â°S, Chile). Boletin del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural 56: 27 - 52" title="Observaciones sobre la flora y vegetacion de los alrededores de Tocopilla (22 Â° S, Chile)." volume="56" year="2007">Luebert et al. (2007)</bibRefCitation>
considered it a Chilean endemic. We hereby extend the distribution of the species to include the populations from the coastal area between 
<normalizedToken id="4AD68F7CA105B7A93EF934AAFC84710E" originalValue="RÃ­o">Rio</normalizedToken>
Loa and Iquique, previously referred to as 
<taxonomicName id="A99FEB32369B174575714F09D982B552" genus="O." lsidName="O. floribundus" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" rank="species" species="floribundus">
<emphasis id="0773004BE96ACE18B29DE5C36A4F8CBC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">O. floribundus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E109A2B8971D2754E91A27A88233B73F" DOI="https://doi.org/10.4067/S0716-078X2001000200014" author="Munoz-Schick, M" journalOrPublisher="Revista Chilena de Historia Natural" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="389 - 405" refId="B10" refString="Munoz-Schick, M, Pinto, R, Mesa, A, Moreira-Munoz, A, 2001. &quot;Oasis de neblina&quot; en los cerros costeros del sur de Iquique, region de Tarapaca, Chile, durante el evento El Nino 1997-1998. Revista Chilena de Historia Natural 74 (2): 389 - 405, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4067/S0716-078X2001000200014" title="&quot; Oasis de neblina &quot; en los cerros costeros del sur de Iquique, region de Tarapaca, Chile, durante el evento El Nino 1997 - 1998." url="https://doi.org/10.4067/S0716-078X2001000200014" volume="74" year="2001">
<normalizedToken id="3FEF24AE457E6085D0FE967A1EEA7E2B" originalValue="MuÃ±oz-Schick">Munoz-Schick</normalizedToken>
et al. 2001
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="6E2656646116123367DB4AFA79AA6F7E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.4067/S0717-66432009000100004" author="Pinto, R" journalOrPublisher="Botanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="28 - 49" refId="B11" refString="Pinto, R, Luebert, F, 2009. Datos sobre la flora vascular del desierto costero de Arica y Tarapaca, Chile, y sus relaciones fitogeograficas con el sur de Peru. Gayana. Botanica 66 (1): 28 - 49, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4067/S0717-66432009000100004" title="Datos sobre la flora vascular del desierto costero de Arica y Tarapaca, Chile, y sus relaciones fitogeograficas con el sur de Peru. Gayana." url="https://doi.org/10.4067/S0717-66432009000100004" volume="66" year="2009">Pinto and Luebert 2009</bibRefCitation>
). See discussion below under the latter species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
